name: EBA Command Center Importable
summary: Learn about .EBAIMPORT files and view a list of programs that open them.

content: EBA Command Center is a Windows application that allows users to create command-based shortcuts to files and websites, as well as execute simple system commands. After installing the program, which is contained in a .VBS script, users can create commands by entering config → cmd → new in EBA Command Center's text box.

In EBA Command Center 7 and later versions, users can export commands and other data in EBAIMPORT files. They can then share these files with other EBA Command Center users, to allow those users to create similar commands.
NOTE: EBA Command Center is discontinued and no longer available.

instructions: To use an EBAIMPORT file to import data into EBA Command Center, open the program, enter the import command, and follow the prompts that appear on-screen. If you want to open and examine an EBAIMPORT file before using it with EBA Command Center (for example, to verify what data it contains), you can do so using any text editor.
